Health
public class Health.SRMLDiagnose
extends DefaultSRMLElement

A subclass to handle the SRML Element diagnose. It will allow a list of modules or all loaded modules to be diagnosed.

The provided attributes are output, level, and all.

Here is an example SRML document that shows how this may be used: 

 <srml>
   <diagnose output="speech" level="full">
     Speech
     UserPanel
   </diagnose>
 </srml>
This will diagnose the modules Speech and UserPanel, outputting the status through speech at full level of diagnostics.

SRMLsetOutput

public void SRMLsetOutput(java.lang.String text)
Called when the attribute output is used. This is used to direct the output of the diagnostic. This can be one of the following:
  • speech -- This is only available if the speech module is loaded.
  • console -- This will return the output back to the ouptput of execute()
  • none -- This will not direct the output back

Parameters:
text - The value of output.

SRMLsetLevel

public void SRMLsetLevel(java.lang.String strLevel)
Called when the attribute level is used. This will set the level of the diagnostic. The level can one of the following:
  • full
  • config
  • default
  • basic

Parameters:
strLevel - The value of level.

SRMLsetAll

public void SRMLsetAll(java.lang.String value)
Called when the attribute all is used. To diagnose all loaded modules, set this to "yes" or "true". Any other value will not diagnose all loaded modules.

Parameters:
value - The value of all.
